th a vacat. The letters are broadly regular and neatly\n                                        cut, but the sizing and spacing varies considerably across the four lines.</p>\n                                    <rs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled</rs>\n                                \t<damage/>\n\t\t\t</layout>\n                            </layoutDesc>\n                        </objectDesc>\n                        <handDesc>\n                            <handNote>\n                                <p>Letters are wide and omicron, phi, sigma, epsilon and theta are, on\n                                    occasion formed by overlarge circles. Epsilon, sigma and omega are lunate. Xsi is\n                                    formed in a distinctive, ornate fashion. Interpuncts are used occasionally, and\n                                    formed of an 's' shape, sometimes forward, sometimes backward facing. Numerals are\n                                    marked with a supraline.</p>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Line 1-4</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">44-62</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Lines 1-4</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">9-27</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina</placeName>\t\t\n                                <placeName type=